name: Handsome Dan: The Most Interesting Dog in the World
description:
"People Don't Rescue HIm, He Rescue's People", while the real Advertisement entertains us with far fetched quotes, - Anyone who has rescued knows that this one isn't an exaggeration. 
Handsome Dan is one of the dogs who was rescued from quarterback Michael Vick's former "Bad Newz Kennels" where he bred and fought pit bull type dogs. 
While many of his rescued brothers and sisters are out at schools and events, serving as breed ambassadors, Handsome Dan prefers to work behind the scenes at "Handsome Dan Rescue" with his rescue mom Heather.  
Please read Handsome Dan's story:
http://www.handsomedansrescue.org

24"x36" 
Limited to 1000 
Each is hand signed and numbered
Printed on archival matte lithography paper (watercolor thickness) 
Ships rolled

name: 42 Dogs Put to Sleep every 6 Minutes Art Rescue Pit bull Awareness
description:
"42 Hearts in 6 Minutes" by Christine J. Head 
Interactive piece -
There are 42 hearts hidden among this inquiring pittie face and his surroundings. How many minutes will it take you to find them all?
In about 6 minutes, 42 animals will be put to sleep in the United States.
This is something that can be just for fun, or upon further explanation, it’s a piece to ponder the overwhelming number of animals that lose their lives each day in the United states. Some of the hearts are very hidden! Christine will have a “cheat sheet” available to those who want it/order the print.

24"x36" & 12"x18"
Limited to 1000
Each is hand signed and numbered
Printed on archival matte lithography paper (watercolor thickness)
Ships rolled

name: Pinky: Saved by Cupcakes!
description:
Pinky" Saved by BadRap & Cupcakes
By Christine J Head


Each Limited to 1000
Signed/numbered by artist
24"x36" (will fit in standard frame)
Now Also available in 12x18 size

When it turned out that Pinky, a Pitbull pulled from a shelter by BadRap.org, needed corrective surgery on both knees - East Bay Vegan Bakers held a Cupcake sale to pay for Pinky's surgery! What a great example of a local business and community coming together to help rescue! 

I have this poster in my 2 year old daughter's room so that she grows up with the reminder of kindness & responsibility to animals, as well as a fine example of creatively helping others. I did the colors to match Pottery Barn pink and green standard gingham/their standard pink/green.
(christine j head watermark will not appear in poster)

If you would like to read more about Pinky, she has her own blog!
http://pinkydeluxe.blogspot.com/
